ful authenticity)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'pa:krifl]"},{"type":"text","text":"inveracious, mendacious, ostensible"},{"type":"entry","text":"valediction","headword":"valediction"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.告别演说，告别词(an address or statement of farewell)"},{"type":"text","text":"[vaelr'drk{n]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：vale（再见）+dict（说）+ion→告别演说，告别词"},{"type":"entry","text":"chimera","headword":"chimera"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.神话怪物(fabulous monster)：梦幻(an impossible or foolish fancy)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kar'mrra]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：原指希腊神话中一种狮头羊身蛇尾的会喷火的妖怪→神话怪物"},{"type":"entry","text":"piecemeal","headword":"piecemeal"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. —件—件的, 零碎的(done, or made piece by piece or in a fragmentary way)"},{"type":"text","text":"['pi:smi:1]"}]},{"number":157,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"trite","headword":"trite"},{"type":"text","text":"adlj.陈腐的，陈词滥调的(hackneyed or boring)"},{"type":"text","text":"[trart]"},{"type":"text","text":"I The plot of this story is so trite that I can predlict the outcome."},{"type":"text","text":"bathetic, commonplace"},{"type":"entry","text":"pithy","headword":"pithy"},{"type":"text","text":"adj（讲话或文章）简练有力的，言简意的（tersely cogent）"},{"type":"text","text":"['prei]"},{"type":"text","text":"concise"},{"type":"entry","text":"bridle","headword":"bridle"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.马笼头(a head harness)v抑制，控制(to curb or control)"},{"type":"text","text":"['brardl]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：和bride（n.新娘）一起记"},{"type":"entry","text":"chase","headword":"chase"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 雕镂(to make a groove in);追逐(to follow rapidly); 追捕"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：谁动了我的奶酪（cheese），我就去追赶（chase）谁"},{"type":"text","text":"[tfers]"},{"type":"entry","text":"dichotomy","headword":"dichotomy"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.两分法；矛盾对立，分歧（bifurcation)：具有两分特征的事物（sth.with seemingly"},{"type":"text","text":"[dar'ka:tami]"},{"type":"text","text":"contradictory qualities)